# Willow environment variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in any non-empty values.
# `.env.local` is gitignored.
#
# Quick start:
#   1. `vercel link` to attach this folder to a Vercel project
#   2. `vercel env pull .env.local` — this writes VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN
#      automatically and you do NOT need any other variable.
#
# OR, if you don't use Vercel right now:
#   - set AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY to a key you generated at
#     https://vercel.com/dashboard → AI → Gateway → API Keys
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── AI Gateway (one of the two below is required) ──

# Recommended: short-lived OIDC token. Provisioned automatically by
# `vercel env pull`. You normally do not edit this by hand.
# VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN=

# Alternative: long-lived API key. Use only if you can't run
# `vercel env pull` (CI environments, non-Vercel hosts).
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=


# ── SME dashboard sign-in (Phase 0 placeholder auth) ──
# All three are optional. Defaults are baked in for local dev so
# you can sign in immediately with `admin` / `admin`. In production
# you SHOULD set all three — particularly SME_SESSION_SECRET, which
# signs the session cookie. Generate with `openssl rand -base64 32`.
# This whole block goes away when we ship Clerk in Phase 4 item 1.
# SME_USERNAME=admin
# SME_PASSWORD=admin
# SME_SESSION_SECRET=
